    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling outing today, led by the elite matchup profile of **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29). Batting leadoff against R. Nelson, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost and favorable winds, making him our cornerstone play for production across all five categories. **Kyle Tucker** (72.71) also presents a strong secondary anchor; while he faces a difficult left-handed arm in D. Peterson, his underlying xwOBA and wind-aided hitting conditions sustain his high floor. Meanwhile, **Josh Lowe** (66.41) provides sneaky value in the bottom third of the order, where a favorable platoon matchup and wind conditions compensate for his lower batting slot to keep his score well within the recommended range.\n\nStrategic lineup construction today hinged on avoiding low-efficiency outcomes against elite arms like Skenes. **Nasim Nunez** (39.49) was the most difficult exclusion from the starting nine; while his speed profile is highly attractive for our SB-starved roster, his inability to clear our 40-point \"Zebras Floor\" against Skenes\u2019 elite 3.10 xERA necessitated a benching to preserve daily caps. We are also monitoring the status of **Luis Robert Jr.** (61.23); his score is bolstered by a significant 14% platoon edge and an aggressive baserunning projection against the slow delivery of Wrobleski, but he remains a high-variance play given the pitcher\u2019s skill. Conversely, **Josh Jung** (60.22) is cleared for a start despite his 8th-order slot, as the +15% SP skill adjustment against L. Severino highlights a prime opportunity for power production. We continue to manage the absences of **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Jordan Westburg** while awaiting internal development from prospects like **Coby Mayo**, **Miguel Vargas**, and **Brady House** to round out the depth of the Austin Waves.",
